{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":6,"author":{"id":"00c7e76c35b172c73e64350c2c5fb2d517134549"},"timestamp":1604029350,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo0NDkxMjYwMzg="},"target":"accebc674b14eb8dea8f1e69befde9af9213b7a09a7559f88f2cc7ad34f6cf54","message":"In some scenarios, we will store some data in xdata. The current geojson file does not contain these data. This function can be added in future versions.\nWhen use dwgread.exe to save as dxf file, it can contain the XData content . but save to geojson file,  will not contain. \n\n```C\n#include \u003cstdio.h\u003e\n#include \u003cstdlib.h\u003e\n\n#include \"dwg.h\"\n#include \"bits.h\"\n\n/**\n * get xdata\n * @param obj Dwg_Object\n */\nvoid object_eed(Dwg_Object *obj) {\n    Dwg_Object_Object *obj_obj = obj-\u003etio.object;\n    for (unsigned i = 0; i \u003c obj_obj-\u003enum_eed; i++) {\n        Dwg_Eed eed = obj_obj-\u003eeed[i];\n        if (eed.size) {\n            Dwg_Object *appid = dwg_resolve_handle(obj_obj-\u003edwg, eed.handle.value);\n            if (appid \u0026\u0026 appid-\u003efixedtype == DWG_TYPE_APPID) {\n                char *name = appid-\u003etio.object-\u003etio.APPID-\u003ename;\n                char *utf8 = bit_convert_TU((BITCODE_TU) name);\n                printf(\"key: %s \\n\", utf8);\n            }\n        }\n\n        if (eed.data) {\n            const Dwg_Eed_Data *data = eed.data;\n            char *str_utf8 = bit_convert_TU((BITCODE_TU) data-\u003eu.eed_0.string);\n            printf(\"%d: %s \\n\", data-\u003ecode, str_utf8);\n            free(str_utf8);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/**\n * read xdata\n * @param filename\n */\nvoid read_xdata(const char *filename) {\n    Dwg_Data dwg;\n    unsigned int opts = 1;\n\n    dwg.opts = opts;\n    dwg_read_file(filename, \u0026dwg);\n\n    for (unsigned i = 0; i \u003c dwg.num_objects; i++) {\n        Dwg_Object obj = dwg.object[i];\n        Dwg_Object_Entity *entity = obj.tio.entity;\n\n        if (obj.supertype != DWG_SUPERTYPE_ENTITY) {\n            continue;\n        }\n        Dwg_Object *layer = entity-\u003elayer ? entity-\u003elayer-\u003eobj : NULL;\n        if (!layer || layer-\u003etype != DWG_TYPE_LAYER) {\n            continue;\n        }\n        object_eed(\u0026obj);\n    }\n    dwg_free(\u0026dwg);\n}\n```\n\n[xdata.dwg.zip](https://github.com/LibreDWG/libredwg/files/5462649/xdata.dwg.zip)","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"00c7e76c35b172c73e64350c2c5fb2d517134549"},"timestamp":1604029383,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo0NDkxMjYyMDY="},"target":"accebc674b14eb8dea8f1e69befde9af9213b7a09a7559f88f2cc7ad34f6cf54","message":"In some scenarios, we will store some data in `xdata`. The current `geojson` file does not contain these data. This function can be added in future versions.\nWhen use `dwgread.exe` to save as `dxf` file, it can contain the `XData` content . but save to `geojson` file,  will not contain. \n\n```C\n#include \u003cstdio.h\u003e\n#include \u003cstdlib.h\u003e\n\n#include \"dwg.h\"\n#include \"bits.h\"\n\n/**\n * get xdata\n * @param obj Dwg_Object\n */\nvoid object_eed(Dwg_Object *obj) {\n    Dwg_Object_Object *obj_obj = obj-\u003etio.object;\n    for (unsigned i = 0; i \u003c obj_obj-\u003enum_eed; i++) {\n        Dwg_Eed eed = obj_obj-\u003eeed[i];\n        if (eed.size) {\n            Dwg_Object *appid = dwg_resolve_handle(obj_obj-\u003edwg, eed.handle.value);\n            if (appid \u0026\u0026 appid-\u003efixedtype == DWG_TYPE_APPID) {\n                char *name = appid-\u003etio.object-\u003etio.APPID-\u003ename;\n                char *utf8 = bit_convert_TU((BITCODE_TU) name);\n                printf(\"key: %s \\n\", utf8);\n            }\n        }\n\n        if (eed.data) {\n            const Dwg_Eed_Data *data = eed.data;\n            char *str_utf8 = bit_convert_TU((BITCODE_TU) data-\u003eu.eed_0.string);\n            printf(\"%d: %s \\n\", data-\u003ecode, str_utf8);\n            free(str_utf8);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n/**\n * read xdata\n * @param filename\n */\nvoid read_xdata(const char *filename) {\n    Dwg_Data dwg;\n    unsigned int opts = 1;\n\n    dwg.opts = opts;\n    dwg_read_file(filename, \u0026dwg);\n\n    for (unsigned i = 0; i \u003c dwg.num_objects; i++) {\n        Dwg_Object obj = dwg.object[i];\n        Dwg_Object_Entity *entity = obj.tio.entity;\n\n        if (obj.supertype != DWG_SUPERTYPE_ENTITY) {\n            continue;\n        }\n        Dwg_Object *layer = entity-\u003elayer ? entity-\u003elayer-\u003eobj : NULL;\n        if (!layer || layer-\u003etype != DWG_TYPE_LAYER) {\n            continue;\n        }\n        object_eed(\u0026obj);\n    }\n    dwg_free(\u0026dwg);\n}\n```\n\n[xdata.dwg.zip](https://github.com/LibreDWG/libredwg/files/5462649/xdata.dwg.zip)","files":null},{"type":5,"author":{"id":"4044e69633a068fb3769d4cf7ce5f6bebf15d0f1"},"timestamp":1604039562,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDM5Mzk3MTEwMzM="},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"4044e69633a068fb3769d4cf7ce5f6bebf15d0f1"},"timestamp":1604039718,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcxOTI4NTQ3MA==","github-url":"https://github.com/LibreDWG/libredwg/issues/281#issuecomment-719285470"},"message":"Only strings? Without checking the type (the group code).\nThere need to be a saner logic and API what APPID's to include, and which data to export from it.\n\nCould you add something like this to the wiki?","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"00c7e76c35b172c73e64350c2c5fb2d517134549"},"timestamp":1604040305,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDcxOTI5NzQ5Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/LibreDWG/libredwg/issues/281#issuecomment-719297493"},"message":"\u003e Only strings? Without checking the type (the group code).\n\u003e There need to be a saner logic and API what APPID's to include, and which data to export from it.\n\u003e \n\u003e Could you add something like this to the wiki?\n\nThe sample codes is 